On Mon, 19 Dec 2005, Ingo Molnar wrote:
> +#define atomic_dec_call_if_negative(v, fn_name)				\
> +do {									\
> +	fastcall void (*__tmp)(atomic_t *) = fn_name;			\
> +									\
> +	(void)__tmp;							\
> +	typecheck(atomic_t *, v);					\
> +									\
> +	__asm__ __volatile__(						\
> +		LOCK "decl (%%rdi)\n"  					\
> +		"js 2f\n"						\
> +		"1:\n"							\
> +		LOCK_SECTION_START("")					\
> +		"2: call "#fn_name"\n\t"				\
> +		"jmp 1b\n"						\
> +		LOCK_SECTION_END					\
> +		:							\
> +		:"D" (v)						\
> +		:"memory");						\
> +} while (0)
Hi Ingo,
	Doesn't this corrupt caller saved registers?
